                    </div>
                    <div class="noidung">
                        <p>50 stalls and 12 miniature production models here represent 12 groups of Vietnamese handicraft villages.<br>

                            Saigon has many favorable conditions for development in all aspects, but in terms of handicrafts, handmade products are passed down from generation to generation, inheriting the spirit and techniques of ancestors. has not yet been cared for and developed. These items require effort, time, and meticulousness, but the profits are small compared to other products.</p>
                        <img src="https://file1.dangcongsan.vn/data/0/images/2020/12/15/kimdung/my-nghe.jpg" height="400px" width="80%"/>
                        <img src="https://laodongthudo.vn/stores/news_dataimages/vuque/082016/21/09/3836_203149_0.jpg"height="400px" width="80%"/>
                        <p>With the desire to contribute a small part to maintaining the quintessence of Vietnamese handicrafts in Saigon, Vietnam House was formed with 50 booths and 12 miniature production models. representing 12 groups of handicraft villages in Vietnam.<br>

                            Products here include bamboo and rattan; products from sedge and water hyacinth; ceramics; wood sculpture; lacquer; embroidery lace; stone sculpture; handmade weaving; construction paper; art picture; metal and other handicraft products. Besides, Vietnam House also has outdoor trial areas to facilitate customers to learn and make their own handicraft products.
                        </p>
                        <img src="https://f.thuongtruong.com.vn/IMAGES/2020/10/26/20201026210511835chap-canh-cho-hang-thu-cong-my-nghe-tai-thi-truong-68-0.jpg" width="80%" height="400px"/>
                        <p>The Vietnamese house has an area of 2,300 m2 next to the Saigon River, creating a convenient space for guests to visit, shop as well as learn and exchange about handicraft village culture. There are more than 2,500 products made by hand by Vietnamese artisans.<br>

                            With a spacious location and airy space, this is an interesting place for customers who are families to visit, shop and entertain during the weekend. Parents can shop while the children participate in outdoor product testing activities and enjoy ethnic music performances from 10:30 a.m. to 11:30 a.m. on Saturdays and Sundays.
                        </p>
